sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Box Inc (Symbol: BOX), where a total of 17,046 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 1.7 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 41.5% of BOX's average daily trading volume over the past month of 4.1 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $25 strike put option expiring December 21, 2018 , with 5,011 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 501,100 underlying shares of BOX.

Below is a chart showing BOX's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $25 strike highlighted in orange:

Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM) saw options trading volume of 22,771 contracts, representing approximately 2.3 million underlying shares or approximately 41.2% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 5.5 million shares.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $157.50 strike put option expiring September 21, 2018 , with 2,670 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 267,000 underlying shares of CRM.

Below is a chart showing CRM's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $157.50 strike highlighted in orange:

And Teradata Corp (Symbol: TDC) options are showing a volume of 3,218 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 321,800 underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 41.1% of TDC's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 782,550 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $40 strike call option expiring October 19, 2018 , with 2,145 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 214,500 underlying shares of TDC.
